Let $p = PP' = PF,$ $q = QQ' = QF,$ $a = P'F',$ and $B = Q'F'.$  Since $P,$ $F,$ and $Q$ are collinear,
\[\frac{p}{q} = \frac{a}{b}.\][asy]
